---

## ðŸ›  Tech Stack

- **Frontend:** React (with Vite), tailwindcss  
- **Backend:** Node.js, Nest.js  
- **Database:** PostgreSQL  
- **ORM:** Prisma  
- **Containerization:** Docker & Docker Compose

---

## ðŸš€ Getting Started

### 1. Clone the repository

git clone https://github.com/nathanAspect/pollAppInternProject
cd rankr-poll-app

### 2. Creat .env file
**create a .env file in the server folder:**

PORT=3000
CLIENT_PORT=8080
POLL_DURATION=7200
JWT_SECRET=thedevilisinthedetails13
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://intern:postgrespassword@localhost:5432/polldb?schema=public"

**create a .env file in the client folder**

VITE_API_HOST=localhost
VITE_API_PORT=3000
VITE_POLLS_NAMESPACE=polls


### 3. Build and Compose
```bash
docker compose up --build
```

The backend server will automatically run Prisma migrations.

The database will initialize with the required tables and will run on port 5432:5432.

Frontend will be available at http://localhost:8080.

Backend API will be available at http://localhost:3000.

